<!-- Tutorial Modals -->
<!-- Use the modals below to showcase details about your tutorial steps! -->

<!-- Tutorial Modal 1 -->
<div class="tutorial-modal modal fade" id="tutorialModal1" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-content">
    <div class="close-modal" data-dismiss="modal">
      <div class="lr">
        <div class="rl">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
          <div class="modal-body">
            <!-- Tutorial Details Go Here -->
            <h2>Step 1: Create your 3D model and animation in Blender</h2>
            <p class="item-intro text-muted">You can use any of the features and tools that Blender offers, such as rigging, sculpting, texturing, lighting, etc. You can also use any of the assets and add-ons that Blender provides, such as characters, environments, materials, etc.</p>
            <img class="img-responsive img-centered" src="img/tutorial/01-full.jpg" alt="">
            <p>In this step, you will create your 3D model and animation in Blender, using the interface and the tools that Blender offers. You can follow these substeps:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Open Blender and create a new file.</li>
              <li>Add a 3D object to your scene, such as a cube, a sphere, a monkey, etc.</li>
              <li>Use the tools in the left panel to transform, edit, and sculpt your object.</li>
              <li>Use the tools in the right panel to add materials, textures, and modifiers to your object.</li>
              <li>Use the tools in the bottom panel to create and edit keyframes for your object's animation.</li>
              <li>Use the tools in the top panel to change the render settings, the output format, and the animation length.</li>
              <li>Use the window menu to switch between different editors, such as the 3D viewport, the UV editor, the node editor, etc.</li>
              <li>Use the help menu to access the documentation, the tutorials, and the community forums.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>You can find more information and tutorials about Blender here: https://www.blender.org/support/</p>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal"><i class="fa fa-times"></i> Close Step</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Tutorial Modal 2 -->
